@page "/tree-grid/menu-filter"

@using Syncfusion.Blazor.TreeGrid
@using Syncfusion.Blazor.Grids
@*Hidden:Lines*@
@using TicketData
@inherits SampleBaseComponent;
@*End:Hidden*@

<SampleDescription>
    <p>This sample demonstrates filtering Tree Grid columns using the filter menu dialog. The dialog opens from each column header's filter icon and allows users to apply conditions for filtering.</p>
</SampleDescription>
<ActionDescription>
    <p>Menu filtering is enabled by setting <a aria-label="Navigate to the AllowFiltering property reference for tree grid component" target="_blank" href="https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/blazor/Syncfusion.Blazor.TreeGrid.SfTreeGrid-1.html#Syncfusion_Blazor_TreeGrid_SfTreeGrid_1_AllowFiltering">AllowFiltering</a> property to <b>true</b> and configuring <a aria-label="Navigate to type property reference for tree grid filter settings" target="_blank" href="https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/blazor/Syncfusion.Blazor.TreeGrid.TreeGridFilterSettings.html#Syncfusion_Blazor_TreeGrid_TreeGridFilterSettings_Type">TreeGridFilterSettings.Type</a> as <code>FilterType.Menu</code>, which shows a filter icon on each header that opens a menu-based dialog for that column.</p>
    <p>Tree Grid supports the following filtering modes using the <a aria-label="Navigate to the HierarchyMode property reference for tree grid filter settings" target="_blank" href="https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/blazor/Syncfusion.Blazor.TreeGrid.TreeGridFilterSettings.html#Syncfusion_Blazor_TreeGrid_TreeGridFilterSettings_HierarchyMode">HierarchyMode</a> property of <code>TreeGridFilterSettings</code>.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><code>Parent</code> - This is the default filter hierarchy mode in Tree Grid. The filtered records appear alongside their parent records. If none of the filtered records have a parent record, only the filtered record itself is displayed.</li>
        <li><code>Child</code> - The filtered records are shown alongside their child records. If the filtered records have no child records, only the filtered records are displayed.</li>
        <li><code>Both</code> - The filtered records are shown alongside their parent and child records. If there are no parent or child records in the filtered records, only the filtered records will be displayed.</li>
        <li><code>None</code> - Only the actual filtered records are displayed.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>In this demo, menu filtering is enabled for all columns, and the hierarchy mode is set to <code>Parent</code>.</p>
    <p>More information about the menu filter can be found in this <a aria-label="Navigate to the documentation for filter menu in the tree grid component" target="_blank" href="https://blazor.syncfusion.com/documentation/treegrid/filtering/filter-menu">documentation</a> section.</p>
</ActionDescription>

<div class="col-lg-12 control-section">
    <div class="content-wrapper">
        <div class="row">
            <SfTreeGrid DataSource="TreeData" AllowFiltering="true" IdMapping="TicketID" ParentIdMapping="ParentTicketID" Height="312" TreeColumnIndex="1">
                <TreeGridFilterSettings Type="Syncfusion.Blazor.TreeGrid.FilterType.Menu"></TreeGridFilterSettings>
                <TreeGridPageSettings PageSize="10"></TreeGridPageSettings>
                <TreeGridColumns>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="TicketID" HeaderText="Ticket ID" Width="150" MinWidth="8" TextAlign="TextAlign.Right"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="Title" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip" HeaderText="Title" Width="300" MinWidth="200"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="Category" HeaderText="Category" Width="135" MinWidth="8"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="CustomerName" HeaderText="Customer Name" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip" Width="170" MinWidth="120"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="Priority" HeaderText="Priority" Width="135" MinWidth="8"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="Status" HeaderText="Status" Width="125" MinWidth="8" TextAlign="TextAlign.Left"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="CreatedDate" HeaderText="Created Date" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip" Width="150" Format="MM/dd/yyyy" Type="ColumnType.Date" />
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="DueDate" HeaderText="Due Date" Width="130" Format="MM/dd/yyyy" Type="ColumnType.Date" />
                </TreeGridColumns>
            </SfTreeGrid>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
@code {

    private List<SupportTicketData> TreeData { get; set; } = new List<SupportTicketData>();

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        TreeData = SupportTicketData.GetSupportTickets();
    }
}